
--------------------DATABASE----------------------------

1. Create MySQL db:
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-the-latest-mysql-on-ubuntu-16-04

2. Go to db: mysql -u root -p

3. See the databases: show databases;

4. To create a database: CREATE DATABASE dbname; //vacationsdb

5. Select database: USE dbname;

6. Create tables (Database have many to many relationships):

	CREATE TABLE employees (
    		id Integer Unsigned Auto_Increment Primary Key,
    		first_name VARCHAR(300) NOT NULL,
    		last_name VARCHAR(300) NOT NULL
    	);

	CREATE TABLE projects (
    		id Integer Unsigned Auto_Increment Primary Key,
    		name VARCHAR(300) NOT NULL
    	);

	CREATE TABLE vacations (
		project_id INTEGER Unsigned NOT NULL,
	    employee_id INTEGER Unsigned NOT NULL,
		start_date DATE,
		end_date DATE,
	    PRIMARY KEY (project_id, employee_id),
	    FOREIGN KEY (project_id) REFERENCES projects (id) ON DELETE RESTRICT ON UPDATE CASCADE,
	    FOREIGN KEY (employee_id) REFERENCES employees (id) ON DELETE RESTRICT ON UPDATE CASCADE
	);

7. List tables: show tables;

8. See table: Describe tableName;

9. Find all projects taken by a given employee:

	SELECT
	    `project`.*
	FROM
	    `project`
	    JOIN `project_employee` ON `project`.`project_id` = `project_employee`.`project`
	WHERE
	    `project_employee`.`employee` = 5678

   Find all employees in the given project:

	SELECT
	    `employee`.*
	FROM
	    `employee`
	    JOIN `project_employee` ON `employee`.`employee_id` = `project_employee`.`employee`
	WHERE
	    `project_employee`.`project` = 1234

10. Insert values:
	INSERT INTO table_name
	VALUES (value1, value2, value3, ...);

11. Different commands:
alter table employees change employee_first_name firstname varchar(100);

--------------------SERVER----------------------------

1. Create serverName folder
2. npm init -y
3. https://www.tutorialspoint.com/nodejs/nodejs_express_framework.htm
   https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HPIjjFGYSJ4
	npm install express --save
	npm install body-parser --save
	npm install cookie-parser --save
(http://localhost:8081/)
mysql -u root -p

--------------------Frontend----------------------------

https://hackernoon.com/how-to-build-a-react-project-from-scratch-using-webpack-4-and-babel-56d4a26afd32


1.  npm init -y
2.  npm install webpack webpack-cli --save-dev
3.  npm install react react-dom --save
4.  npm install @babel/core babel-loader @babel/preset-env @babel/preset-react --save-dev
5.  vim index.js ./src
6.  vim index.html ./src
7.  vim webpack.config.js ./vacations
8.  npm install css-loader style-loader --save-dev
9.  vim .babelrc ./vacations
10. Add scripts in package.json:
	"start": "webpack --mode development --watch",
	"build": "webpack --mode production"
11. vim App.js ./src/components
12. vim App.css ./src/styles

